President Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama hosted an event at the White House on September 16, 2009, to promote Chicago's bid for the 2016 Summer Olympic and Paralympic Games. The event highlighted the Obama administration's commitment to service, healthy living, and youth sports. The President and First Lady were joined by Chicago Mayor Richard Daley, representatives from Chicago2016 and the United States Olympic Committee (USOC), as well as Olympians and Paralympians. The athletes visited DC area schools in the morning and then returned to the White House for the event. After the President and First Lady's remarks, sports demonstrations took place. The First Lady was also announced to lead the delegation to support Chicago's bid at the host city election in Copenhagen.